# Auth Error Handling

## Line → Supabase OAuth flow

```
User clicks "Login with Line"
  → Redirect to Line authorization URL (with state + PKCE code_verifier)
  → Line redirects to NEXT_PUBLIC_LINE_CALLBACK_URL (/api/auth/callback)
  → Callback: validate state param, exchange Line code for Line access token
  → Use Line access token to create/sign-in Supabase user
  → Redirect to app
```

**Note:** This is a custom flow — do NOT use `supabase.auth.signInWithOAuth()` for Line.

## Callback route requirements

Every `/api/auth/callback` handler must:

```ts
// 1. Check for error from Line
const error = searchParams.get("error");
if (error) {
  redirect(`/auth/error?reason=${error}`);
}

// 2. Validate state param (CSRF protection)
const state = searchParams.get("state");
const storedState = cookies().get("oauth_state")?.value;
if (!state || state !== storedState) {
  redirect("/auth/error?reason=state_mismatch");
}

// 3. Exchange code (expires in 10 minutes)
const code = searchParams.get("code");
if (!code) {
  redirect("/auth/error?reason=missing_code");
}
```

## Server-side API routes

Always verify session before reading user:

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
const { data: { session } } = await supabase.auth.getSession();
if (!session) return NextResponse.json({ error: { code: "UNAUTHORIZED" } }, { status: 401 });
const userId = session.user.id;

// ❌ BAD
const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser(); // may return null without redirect
```

## Redirect URI

`NEXT_PUBLIC_LINE_CALLBACK_URL` must exactly match the URL registered in Line Developer Console — including protocol, domain, and path. Any mismatch causes a silent auth failure.

## Local dev bypass

`TEST_MODE_AUTH_BYPASS=true` in `.env.local` skips the Line auth flow for local development. This flag must never be set in production. API routes must check:

```ts
if (process.env.TEST_MODE_AUTH_BYPASS === "true" && process.env.NODE_ENV !== "production") {
  // use test user
}
```

## Rule

- Every auth callback → validates state, handles error param, handles missing/expired code
- Every API route → checks session before reading user
- Never assume authenticated state without verification
